Cable Incline Chest Press

ExRx.net > Directory > Upper Chest > Exercise

請選取語言​▼

Classification

Utility: Basic or Auxiliary
Mechanics: Compound
Force: Push

Instructions

Preparation

Sit on seat and grasp stirrups attached to medium height pulleys on each side. Position elbows out to sides, slightly lower than shoulder height. Position hands slightly above shoulder height and narrower than elbow width.

Execution

Push stirrups away from body, slightly upward at 30º to 45º until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

Comments

Stirrup should follow slight arch pattern, in front/above of upper arm between elbow and chest in stretched position, travelling inward in front/above each shoulder at contracted position. See Cable Incline Chest Press performed on older machine.

Muscles

Target

  • Pectoralis Major, Clavicular

Synergists

  • Pectoralis Major, Sternal
  • Deltoid, Anterior
  • Triceps Brachii
  • Coracobrachialis

Dynamic Stabilizers

  • Biceps Brachii, Short Head
